:R-HSA-163765  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0009893 ;
        rdfs:comment        "ChREBP (Carbohydrate Response Element Binding Protein) is a large multidomain protein containing a nuclear localization signal near its amino terminus, polyproline domains, a basic helix-loop-helix-leucine zipper domain, and a leucine-zipper-like domain (Uyeda et al., 2002). Its dephosphorylation in response to molecular signals associated with the well-fed state allows it to enter the nucleus, interact with MLX protein, and bind to ChRE DNA sequence motifs near Acetyl-CoA carboxylase, Fatty acid synthase, and Pyruvate kinase (L isoform) genes (Ishi et al.2004). This sequence of events is outlined schematically in the picture below (adapted from Kawaguchi et al. (2001) - copyright (2001) National Academy of Sciences, U.S.A.)." ;
        rdfs:label          "ChREBP activates metabolic gene expression" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Hill, David P, 2024-02-12" , "Authored: Gopinathrao, G, 2005-05-12 21:32:40" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-163765" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-163685/R-HSA-163685> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

